  "prompt": "Does Microsoft own Google?",
  "response": "No, Microsoft does not own Google. Both companies are independent and compete in various sectors of the tech industry. \n\n- **Microsoft** was founded in 1975 by Bill Gates and Paul Allen and is known for products like Windows, Office, and Azure.  \n- **Google** was founded in 1998 by Larry Page and Sergey Brin and is a subsidiary of Alphabet Inc. (created in 2015). It dominates in search, Android, and digital advertising.  \n\nWhile both have made significant acquisitions (e.g., Microsoft owns LinkedIn and GitHub; Google owns YouTube and Android), they operate separately. Microsoft's search engine, **Bing**, competes directly with **Google Search**, and their cloud platforms (Azure vs. Google Cloud) are rivals. Neither holds a controlling stake in the other. \n\nIn summary, they are distinct entities with no ownership ties.",
